      var context = this, args = arguments;
      var later = function() {

<script type="text/javascript">
// NOTE: Wrong debug value is causing some issues with our ad debugger, so clearing it to fix the issue
(function flushDebugStorage(){
  try {
    var keyToRemove = 'debug';
    if (window.localStorage && localStorage.getItem(keyToRemove) !== null) {
      localStorage.removeItem(keyToRemove);
      return;
    }
  } catch (e) {
    console.log('error while flushing debug storage');
  }
})();
</script>
<script type="text/javascript">
  window.HPGam = window.HPGam || {};
  window.HPGam.cmd = window.HPGam.cmd || [];
  window.googletag = window.googletag || {};
  window.googletag.cmd = window.googletag.cmd || [];
  
  function getCookie(cookieName) {
    var cookies = document.cookie.split(';');
    for (var i = 0; i < cookies.length; i++) {
      var cookie = cookies[i].trim();
      if (cookie.startsWith(cookieName + '=')) {
        return cookie.substring(cookieName.length + 1);
      }
    }
    return null;
  }

  HPGam.cmd.push(function(){
    var brandPlatform = [];
    var renderer = 'unknown';
    var platform = '';

    var geo = '';
    var geoZoneMap = {
      "uk": "uk.huffpost"
    };

    var zoneOne = geoZoneMap[geo] || 'huffpost';
    brandPlatform.push(zoneOne);

    
    platform = 'desktop';
    brandPlatform.push('desktop');
    
    
    var category = 'unknown';
    
    category = 'home';
    

    
    renderer = 'cambria';
    
    
    
    

    var networkID = '6556';
    

    var testAdStr = "".replace(/\s*/g, '');
    var testAds = testAdStr.length > 0 ? testAdStr.split(",") : [];
    var affiliateCookie = getCookie('bf-affiliate');

    HPGam.env.setParams({
      abData: [],
      bnp: "",
      brandPlatform: brandPlatform.join('.'),
      entryId: "",
      geo: geo,
      locale: 'en',
      networkID: networkID,
      pageTypes: ["atf","front","homepage","vert_front"],
      platform: platform,
      platformNames: ["cambria"],
      section: category,
      site: "us",
      subSections: [],
      tags: [],
      testAds: testAds,
      wCategory: [],
      wKeyword: [],
      wSentiment: [],
      authorNickname: "",
      category: "premium",
      affiliateCookie: affiliateCookie,
      cat: ""
    });

    function targetMap() {
      function csvToArr(str) {
        var str2 = str.replace(/(^\s+|\s+$)/g, '');
        return (str2.length && str2.split(",") || []);
      }
      var r = [];
      function addKV(key, val) {
        if (val.length > 0) {
          r.push([key, val]);
        }
      }
      addKV("destination", "huffpost");
      addKV("edition", "us");
      addKV("hpid", "");
      
      addKV("zone3", "home");
      
      addKV("section", csvToArr(""));
      
      addKV("pageType", "A");
      
      addKV("cms_tag", csvToArr(""));
      
      
      addKV("user", csvToArr(""));
      var dfpKeywordVal = HPGam.getQuery("dfp-keyword");
      if (dfpKeywordVal) {
        addKV('dfp-keyword', dfpKeywordVal);
      }
      if (renderer) {
        addKV('renderer', renderer);
      }
      
 
      addKV('w_category',csvToArr(""));
      addKV('w_keyword',csvToArr(""));
      addKV('w_sentiment',csvToArr(""));
                               
      addKV("cat", "");
                               
      var affiliateCookie = getCookie('bf-affiliate');
      if (affiliateCookie) {
        addKV("affiliate", affiliateCookie);
      }
 
      return r;
    }

    googletag.cmd.push(function(){
      var map = targetMap();
      HPGam.log('setTargeting', map);
      map.forEach(function(t){
        return googletag.pubads().setTargeting(t[0], t[1]);
      });
    });

    return;
  });
</script>

<script>
window.waitForGlobal = function(identifier, cb, poll) {
  var test = typeof identifier === "function" ? identifier : function() { return !!window[identifier]; };
  var interval;
  if(test()) {
    cb();
  } else {
    interval = setInterval(function(){
      if(test()) {
        cb();
        clearInterval(interval);
      }
    }, poll || 50);
  }
};

window.modulousQueue = (function() {
  var queue = [];
  var run = false;
  function runner(fn) {
    setTimeout(function(){
      try {
        fn();
      } catch (e) {
      }
    }, 0);
  }
  return {
     add: function(fn) {
       var _tmp1 = !run && queue.push(fn);
       var _tmp2 = run && runner(fn);
     },
     runAll: function() {
       var i = 0;
       run = true;
       for(;i<queue.length;i++) {
         runner(queue[i]);
       }
       queue = [];
     }
  };
}());

setTimeout(function(){
  waitForGlobal('jQuery', modulousQueue.runAll);
}, 5000);

He started his career in journalism more than 20 years ago, cutting his teeth on local newspapers in the South West of England. In 2010, he moved to London to report on the U.K. parliament. The Republican-controlled state, following a push by President Donald Trump, are seeking to shift congressional district borders such that five seats flip from Democratic control. The contentious but legally permitted move, known as partisan gerrymandering, seeks to prevent Republicans from losing control of the US House of Representatives in next year&#x27;s midterms, when the opposition party usually does more favorably. Dozens of Democrats in the Texas legislature faced threats of legal action Monday after they fled the state to block a redrawing of districts in Republicans&#x27; favor ahead of the 2026 midterm elections. The Republican-controlled state, following a push by President Donald Trump, are seeking to shift congressional district borders such that five seats flip from Democratic control. The contentious but legally permitted move, known as partisan gerrymandering, seeks to prevent Republicans from losing control of the US House of Representatives in next year&#x27;s midterms, when the opposition party usually does more favorably. Dozens of Democrats in the Texas legislature faced threats of legal action Monday after they fled the state to block a redrawing of districts in Republicans&#x27; favor ahead of the 2026 midterm elections. The Republican-controlled state, following a push by President Donald Trump, are seeking to shift congressional district borders such that five seats flip from Democratic control. The contentious but legally permitted move, known as partisan gerrymandering, seeks to prevent Republicans from losing control of the US House of Representatives in next year&#x27;s midterms, when the opposition party usually does more favorably. </div></div><div class="front-support-huffpost-container js-cet-subunit"><div class="front-support-huffpost"><div class="front-support-huffpost__text-container support-huffpost__message--main"><div class="front-support-huffpost__headline"><span class="front-support-huffpost__headline--first">MAGA makes</span><span class="front-support-huffpost__headline--second">&#x27;your mom&#x27;</span><span class="front-support-huffpost__headline--third">jokes.</span></div><div class="front-support-huffpost__sub-headline">We make headlines.</div><p>Serious questions deserve better than middle school humor. </p></div><div class="front-support-huffpost__text-container support-huffpost__message--main variation contributor-once-variation"><div class="front-support-huffpost__headline"><span class="front-support-huffpost__headline--first">Your Support</span><span class="front-support-huffpost__headline--second">Fuels</span><span class="front-support-huffpost__headline--third">Our Mission</span></div><p>We remain committed to providing you with the unflinching, fact-based journalism everyone deserves.<br/><br/>Thank you again for your support along the way. Dozens of Democrats in the Texas legislature faced threats of legal action Monday after they fled the state to block a redrawing of districts in Republicans&#x27; favor ahead of the 2026 midterm elections. The Republican-controlled state, following a push by President Donald Trump, are seeking to shift congressional district borders such that five seats flip from Democratic control. The contentious but legally permitted move, known as partisan gerrymandering, seeks to prevent Republicans from losing control of the US House of Representatives in next year&#x27;s midterms, when the opposition party usually does more favorably. Kalish is a reporter covering LGBTQ+ rights at HuffPost. They cover how state and federal policies impact the lived experiences of LGBTQ+ people and people living with HIV — and how laws regulating gender, sex, bodily autonomy, and privacy impact everyone. Their reporting ranges from explainers on health care law, to investigations into right-wing figures shaping the conservative anti-trans movement, to features on LGBTQ+ people navigating the current political landscape. Before joining HuffPost in 2023, Lil covered LGBTQ+ rights at BuzzFeed News, wrote about inequality at CalMatters, and reported on tech and California politics at Mother Jones. Lil first cut their teeth as a reporter covering arts, culture, and political censorship at The Myanmar Times, formerly Myanmar’s only English-language daily newspaper. Lil’s reporting has taken them from the deserts of Southern California to the streets of Yangon and appears in The Los Angeles Times, The Guardian, LAist, ARTNews and elsewhere. They have given talks at Stanford, Bowdoin and USC, and have appeared on radio segments for Vox’s “Record” and NPR’s “It’s Been a Minute.” Lil believes in reporting “at the speed of trust,” to borrow a phrase from adrienne maree brown. You can reach them at lil.kalish@huffpost.com. Brian Schatz (D-Hawaii) slams Trump admin spending habits amid shut down&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;C-SPAN&quot;,&quot;height&quot;:1798,&quot;width&quot;:2940,&quot;ops&quot;:&quot;500_281&quot;,&quot;keepOriginalQuality&quot;:true},&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Democratic Senator Casually Dismantles GOP’s Stunning Hypocrisy On Spending&quot;,&quot;titleOrigin&quot;:&quot;user&quot;},&quot;winningVariationId&quot;:10702472},&quot;68f9112ee4b01e35ba16dae2&quot;:{&quot;active&quot;:false,&quot;id&quot;:1434754,&quot;resolved&quot;:true,&quot;status&quot;:&quot;resolved&quot;,&quot;variationCount&quot;:4,&quot;variations&quot;:[{&quot;id&quot;:10701905,&quot;image&quot;:{&quot;url&quot;:{&quot;fileName&quot;:&quot;68f91160180000c05be8efc1.jpeg&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;hectorUrl&quot;},&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;Texas Representative Jasmine Crockett speaks in front of Democratic members of Congress and Texas House Democrats during a news conference, after they left their state to deny Republicans the quorum needed to redraw the state&#x27;s 38 congressional districts, at IBEW Local Union 701 on August 4, 2025 in Warrenville, Illinois. Dozens of Democrats in the Texas legislature faced threats of legal action Monday after they fled the state to block a redrawing of districts in Republicans&#x27; favor ahead of the 2026 midterm elections. The Republican-controlled state, following a push by President Donald Trump, are seeking to shift congressional district borders such that five seats flip from Democratic control. The contentious but legally permitted move, known as partisan gerrymandering, seeks to prevent Republicans from losing control of the US House of Representatives in next year&#x27;s midterms, when the opposition party usually does more favorably. (Photo by KAMIL KRZACZYNSKI / AFP) (Photo by KAMIL KRZACZYNSKI/AFP via Getty Images)          &quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;KAMIL KRZACZYNSKI via Getty Images&quot;,&quot;height&quot;:3867,&quot;width&quot;:5800,&quot;ops&quot;:&quot;500_281&quot;,&quot;keepOriginalQuality&quot;:true},&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Jasmine Crockett Teases Senate Bid&quot;,&quot;titleOrigin&quot;:&quot;user&quot;},{&quot;id&quot;:10701906,&quot;image&quot;:{&quot;url&quot;:{&quot;fileName&quot;:&quot;68f91160180000c05be8efc1.jpeg&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;hectorUrl&quot;},&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;Texas Representative Jasmine Crockett speaks in front of Democratic members of Congress and Texas House Democrats during a news conference, after they left their state to deny Republicans the quorum needed to redraw the state&#x27;s 38 congressional districts, at IBEW Local Union 701 on August 4, 2025 in Warrenville, Illinois. Dozens of Democrats in the Texas legislature faced threats of legal action Monday after they fled the state to block a redrawing of districts in Republicans&#x27; favor ahead of the 2026 midterm elections. The Republican-controlled state, following a push by President Donald Trump, are seeking to shift congressional district borders such that five seats flip from Democratic control. The contentious but legally permitted move, known as partisan gerrymandering, seeks to prevent Republicans from losing control of the US House of Representatives in next year&#x27;s midterms, when the opposition party usually does more favorably. Dozens of Democrats in the Texas legislature faced threats of legal action Monday after they fled the state to block a redrawing of districts in Republicans&#x27; favor ahead of the 2026 midterm elections. The Republican-controlled state, following a push by President Donald Trump, are seeking to shift congressional district borders such that five seats flip from Democratic control. The contentious but legally permitted move, known as partisan gerrymandering, seeks to prevent Republicans from losing control of the US House of Representatives in next year&#x27;s midterms, when the opposition party usually does more favorably. Dozens of Democrats in the Texas legislature faced threats of legal action Monday after they fled the state to block a redrawing of districts in Republicans&#x27; favor ahead of the 2026 midterm elections. The Republican-controlled state, following a push by President Donald Trump, are seeking to shift congressional district borders such that five seats flip from Democratic control. The contentious but legally permitted move, known as partisan gerrymandering, seeks to prevent Republicans from losing control of the US House of Representatives in next year&#x27;s midterms, when the opposition party usually does more favorably.
